description:
Microsoft Clip Organizer was a clip art organizing software, which allowed users to find drawings, photographs, sounds, videos, and other media clips to include in presentations, publications, and other Office documents. It cam with a variety of stock media clips and offered more selection on the Microsoft Office Online website.
(source: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft_Office_shared_tools#Clip_Organizer)

Among these stock media clips, were several MIDI files, which are being played in this vdieo. I used VLC Media Player and FluidSynth with a Microsoft GS Wavetable Synth soundfont to convert these into wave files, which I am playing with a simple batch script.

* Thumbnail graphics *
Midi icons created by Dimitry Miroliubov - Flaticon (https://www.flaticon.com/free-icons/midi)
Clip Organizer window illustration from: https://bettersolutions.com/powerpoint/illustrations/clip-organiser.htm

* Other links *
Batch file: https://pastebin.com/8cHWTR4b
Original MIDI files are available on archive.org, under the Microsoft Clip Art archive: https://archive.org/download/MS_Clipart_Collection (almost all of the songs are from this archive, except for Techno Dance, which I had saved myself)

comments.text: I remember vibing to these on my family's Windows 98 in the mid-late 2000s. Such was the entertainment for a kid who wasnt allowed on the internet!
comments.author: @applesauceisnotacolour3173

comments.text:
can i get the names of the corresponding files?
they're all within this format for some reason "M###########", and i cant tell which is which, so it would be really helpful if some sort of text file, or anything to identify each of the files could be made, thanks!
comments.author: @TFB2K-baubau

comments.text:
1. Go to web.archive.org
2. Search for a URL in this format: http://office.microsoft.com/en-us/images/MS<a bunch of numbers>.aspx (e.g. for MS900437885, it would be http://office.microsoft.com/en-us/images/MS900437885.aspx and we can see that the actual name is "Strength of Spirit")
3. If you're lucky, you might see a capture with the actual name of the song/image
comments.author: @PAKTC
